history.text: Hi! This sounds like a very interesting movie! What do you think?
Hi are you there?
It is good! It scored well with critics too
I really like Kristen Bell and think she did great in this role! I thought she was the singer
I love movies about fearless princesses. It really shows true girl power and teaches young girls they can accomplish anything!
It also helped Disney to build its modern animation department! They haven't had a hit like it since Little Mermaid and Beauty and the Beast
This would make a great Broadway musical considering how well the music is styled
Yeah! Did you know it was based of Hans Christian Andersen's "The Snow Queen" ?
That's so awesome! And the directors Chris Buck and Jennifer Lee really did a great job bringing it to life!
Can't believe its already been out for 5 years!
l always get Ana and Elsa confused. Anna is the younger sister and Elsa is the Queen
are you there?
Can you believe Elsa became queen at the age of 21?
Thats so young!
I was so sad for the girls when they were separated at such a young age from Elsa's accidental magic.
It's so sad that the girls were isolated to the castle because of Elsa's ice powers
Luckily Anna didn't remember
And so sad that their parents died at sea because of a storm.
Luckily they were there to take them to the trolls to save them before they left though!

Yes! Can you imagine how scary it was to realize your sister had ice powers, and she was the reason for the eternal
 winter in the kingdom?
Elsa's cycokinetic magic was fun for them to play with though before.
That's true. What did you think about Anna falling in love with Prince Hans?
I was concerned when they quickly decided to get married and thought ELsa was right to object
Oh definitely! I completely agree! It didn't help that the two sisters were already distant.
They may had been alright had Elsa not accidentally revealed her powers when she objected
I hate that the Duke called her a monster. If only he knew the whole story!
I know that Elsa didn't mean to freeze Anna's heart but Elsa really needs to learn to control her anger!
I couldn't believe it when they show that Hans has been evil this whole time!
And how cruel of Hans to have used Anna like that! At least he showed his true colors before it was too late
And luckily Elsa gets away!
Hans was the real monster in this story.
Yes he was and I liked Kristoff better anyways!
Oh yes!
He saved Anna so many times!
They were truly meant for each other! I really liked how the story turned and took us all by surprise that Hans was not the one for Anna!
He was only interested in the throne!
The "act of true love" took me by surprise too! I thought for sure it would be a kiss from Hans until he turned out to be evil.
I loved how the act of true love wasn't just a kiss like other movies!
Though i was surprised too
Yes that really set this movie apart!
It sure did!
Do you typically watch animated movies like this?
Yes i love animation
I was afraid Anna would freeze solid before the act of true love!
